#: src/data/wiki/categories/salary-negotiation.ts
msgid "A typical counter-offer is 10 to 20 percent above the initial offer, depending on how far below market rate the offer is. Your counter should be grounded in research data, not an arbitrary percentage. If the offer is already near the top of the market range, a modest counter of 5 to 10 percent is more appropriate. The key is that your number should be justifiable with data."
msgstr "A typical counter-offer is 10 to 20 percent above the initial offer, depending on how far below market rate the offer is. Your counter should be grounded in research data, not an arbitrary percentage. If the offer is already near the top of the market range, a modest counter of 5 to 10 percent is more appropriate. The key is that your number should be justifiable with data."

