#: src/data/wiki/categories/cover-letters.ts
msgid ""
"A well-structured cover letter follows a clear, logical flow that guides the reader from your introduction through your qualifications and into a compelling call to action. The standard cover letter structure consists of four key components: the header, opening paragraph, body paragraphs, and closing paragraph. Each serves a distinct purpose and should be crafted with intention.\n"
"\n"
"Your header should include your full name, contact information, the date, and the recipient's details. Keep this professional and consistent with the formatting of your resume to create a cohesive application package. Many applicants use a matching header design across both documents, which creates a polished, branded appearance.\n"
"\n"
"The opening paragraph is your hook -- it should immediately capture attention and establish why you are writing. The body paragraphs (typically one or two) are where you present your strongest qualifications, tell relevant stories, and draw direct connections between your experience and the job requirements. The closing paragraph should reiterate your enthusiasm, include a clear call to action, and thank the reader for their consideration.\n"
"\n"
"Throughout the letter, maintain a professional but personable tone. Write in the first person and use active voice to convey confidence and energy. Avoid passive constructions like \"the project was managed by me\" in favor of direct statements like \"I managed a cross-functional project that delivered a 30% increase in operational efficiency.\" Every sentence should serve a purpose -- if it does not add value, remove it.\n"
"\n"
"Aim for a length of three to four paragraphs, fitting comfortably on a single page. Most hiring managers spend less than a minute reviewing a cover letter, so every word needs to earn its place. White space and clear paragraph breaks improve readability and make your key points easier to scan."
msgstr ""
"A well-structured cover letter follows a clear, logical flow that guides the reader from your introduction through your qualifications and into a compelling call to action. The standard cover letter structure consists of four key components: the header, opening paragraph, body paragraphs, and closing paragraph. Each serves a distinct purpose and should be crafted with intention.\n"
"\n"
