"\n"
"Throughout the letter, maintain a professional but personable tone. Write in the first person and use active voice to convey confidence and energy. Avoid passive constructions like \"the project was managed by me\" in favor of direct statements like \"I managed a cross-functional project that delivered a 30% increase in operational efficiency.\" Every sentence should serve a purpose -- if it does not add value, remove it.\n"
"\n"
"Aim for a length of three to four paragraphs, fitting comfortably on a single page. Most hiring managers spend less than a minute reviewing a cover letter, so every word needs to earn its place. White space and clear paragraph breaks improve readability and make your key points easier to scan."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/interview-preparation.ts
msgid "A well-structured STAR response should take between one and two minutes to deliver. Spend roughly fifteen percent on the Situation, fifteen percent on the Task, fifty percent on the Action, and twenty percent on the Result. If the interviewer wants more detail, they will ask follow-up questions. Keeping your initial response concise shows respect for their time and strong communication skills."
msgstr "A well-structured STAR response should take between one and two minutes to deliver. Spend roughly fifteen percent on the Situation, fifteen percent on the Task, fifty percent on the Action, and twenty percent on the Result. If the interviewer wants more detail, they will ask follow-up questions. Keeping your initial response concise shows respect for their time and strong communication skills."

