#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-fundamentals.ts
msgid "Absolutely. A two-page resume is appropriate for professionals with 10 or more years of experience, senior-level candidates, technical roles requiring extensive skills listings, or anyone whose relevant qualifications genuinely require additional space. The key is that every line on both pages should contain relevant, impactful content. A strong two-page resume is always better than a cramped one-page resume that sacrifices readability, and always better than a padded two-page resume full of irrelevant information."
msgstr "Absolutely. A two-page resume is appropriate for professionals with 10 or more years of experience, senior-level candidates, technical roles requiring extensive skills listings, or anyone whose relevant qualifications genuinely require additional space. The key is that every line on both pages should contain relevant, impactful content. A strong two-page resume is always better than a cramped one-page resume that sacrifices readability, and always better than a padded two-page resume full of irrelevant information."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/salary-negotiation.ts
msgid "Absolutely. Employers expect negotiation at all levels, including entry-level. Only about 20 percent of new graduates negotiate, which means the other 80 percent leave money on the table. A polite, research-backed negotiation is always appropriate and is often respected by hiring managers as a sign of professionalism and self-awareness."
msgstr "Absolutely. Employers expect negotiation at all levels, including entry-level. Only about 20 percent of new graduates negotiate, which means the other 80 percent leave money on the table. A polite, research-backed negotiation is always appropriate and is often respected by hiring managers as a sign of professionalism and self-awareness."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-formats.ts
msgid "Absolutely. In fact, tailoring your resume format to each application is a best practice. You might use a chronological format when applying to a traditional corporate role, a combination format when targeting a position that requires specific transferable skills, and a creative format when applying to a design-focused company. Maintaining a master resume document with all of your experiences makes it easy to create format-specific versions for each opportunity."
msgstr "Absolutely. In fact, tailoring your resume format to each application is a best practice. You might use a chronological format when applying to a traditional corporate role, a combination format when targeting a position that requires specific transferable skills, and a creative format when applying to a design-focused company. Maintaining a master resume document with all of your experiences makes it easy to create format-specific versions for each opportunity."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/job-search-strategies.ts
msgid "Absolutely. Review the interviewer's LinkedIn profile to understand their background, tenure at the company, career path, and any shared connections or experiences. This helps you build rapport, ask relevant questions, and tailor your responses to their perspective. Do not mention that you researched them explicitly, but use the information to guide conversation naturally."
msgstr "Absolutely. Review the interviewer's LinkedIn profile to understand their background, tenure at the company, career path, and any shared connections or experiences. This helps you build rapport, ask relevant questions, and tailor your responses to their perspective. Do not mention that you researched them explicitly, but use the information to guide conversation naturally."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/salary-negotiation.ts
msgid "Absolutely. Total compensation including base salary, bonuses, equity, and benefits is what matters for comparing opportunities. In many industries, variable compensation represents 20 to 50 percent of total pay, so focusing only on base salary can significantly undervalue or overvalue a position."
msgstr "Absolutely. Total compensation including base salary, bonuses, equity, and benefits is what matters for comparing opportunities. In many industries, variable compensation represents 20 to 50 percent of total pay, so focusing only on base salary can significantly undervalue or overvalue a position."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/ats-optimization.ts
msgid "Absolutely. While required qualifications carry the most weight in ATS scoring, preferred qualifications also contribute to your overall match score. Including keywords from the preferred section can elevate your ranking above candidates who only match the required criteria. If you have experience with any of the preferred qualifications, include them in your resume. Even if you do not meet all preferred requirements, including some of these keywords demonstrates additional value and can differentiate you from other applicants."
msgstr "Absolutely. While required qualifications carry the most weight in ATS scoring, preferred qualifications also contribute to your overall match score. Including keywords from the preferred section can elevate your ranking above candidates who only match the required criteria. If you have experience with any of the preferred qualifications, include them in your resume. Even if you do not meet all preferred requirements, including some of these keywords demonstrates additional value and can differentiate you from other applicants."

