msgid "As a fresh graduate, a one-page resume is almost always the right choice. Focus on your education, relevant coursework, internships, part-time jobs, academic projects, volunteer work, and skills. Highlight transferable skills from any experience, even if it was not in your target field. A campus leadership role demonstrates management skills; a retail job shows customer service and communication skills. Use a professional summary that emphasizes your education, enthusiasm, and the value you can bring rather than dwelling on your limited experience."
