#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-formats.ts
msgid "Functional resumes are generally less ATS-friendly than chronological resumes. Most applicant tracking systems are optimized to parse resumes that follow a standard chronological structure with job titles, company names, and dates clearly associated with each position. The skills-based organization of a functional resume can confuse these systems, potentially causing important information to be miscategorized or missed entirely. If you are applying to companies that use ATS, consider using a combination format instead."
msgstr "Functional resumes are generally less ATS-friendly than chronological resumes. Most applicant tracking systems are optimized to parse resumes that follow a standard chronological structure with job titles, company names, and dates clearly associated with each position. The skills-based organization of a functional resume can confuse these systems, potentially causing important information to be miscategorized or missed entirely. If you are applying to companies that use ATS, consider using a combination format instead."

