#: src/data/wiki/categories/industry-guides.ts
msgid "Include your GPA if it is 3.0 or higher on a 4.0 scale, or the equivalent in your grading system. If your major GPA is significantly higher than your cumulative GPA, you may list your major GPA instead. After two to three years of professional experience, GPA becomes less relevant and can be removed."
msgstr "Include your GPA if it is 3.0 or higher on a 4.0 scale, or the equivalent in your grading system. If your major GPA is significantly higher than your cumulative GPA, you may list your major GPA instead. After two to three years of professional experience, GPA becomes less relevant and can be removed."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/career-transitions.ts
msgid "Include your rank in parentheses alongside a translated civilian job title, such as \"Senior Operations Manager (E-7/Sergeant First Class).\" This gives civilian readers an immediate understanding of your role while providing context for those familiar with military rank structures. Avoid using rank as your primary job title, as many civilian recruiters will not understand it."
msgstr "Include your rank in parentheses alongside a translated civilian job title, such as \"Senior Operations Manager (E-7/Sergeant First Class).\" This gives civilian readers an immediate understanding of your role while providing context for those familiar with military rank structures. Avoid using rank as your primary job title, as many civilian recruiters will not understand it."

