"\n"
"For positions at companies you are particularly interested in, go beyond the Easy Apply submission. Find the hiring manager or a team member on LinkedIn and send a thoughtful connection request or InMail expressing your interest. Reference the specific job posting, briefly explain why you are an excellent fit, and mention one insight about the company that demonstrates you have done your research. This direct outreach can move your application from the pile of hundreds of Easy Apply submissions to the shortlist of candidates the hiring manager reviews personally."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/job-search-strategies.ts
msgid ""
"LinkedIn has evolved from a professional networking site into the most comprehensive job search platform available, combining job listings, recruiter access, company research, and professional networking in a single ecosystem. Optimizing your LinkedIn presence is no longer optional for job seekers; it is the foundation of a modern job search strategy.\n"
"\n"
"Your LinkedIn profile serves double duty as both a resume and a searchable professional webpage. Recruiters use LinkedIn Recruiter to search for candidates based on keywords, skills, location, and experience. Ensure your profile includes the keywords that recruiters in your industry search for, particularly in your headline, summary, and experience sections. A headline like \"Senior Data Scientist specializing in NLP and Machine Learning\" is infinitely more searchable than \"Looking for new opportunities.\"\n"
"\n"
"Use the Open to Work feature strategically. This feature signals to recruiters that you are actively looking, which increases your visibility in recruiter searches. You can choose to display it to all LinkedIn members or only to recruiters. If you are searching confidentially while employed, the recruiter-only setting protects your privacy while still broadcasting your availability to the people who can help.\n"
"\n"
"Set up customized job alerts with specific keywords, locations, and company filters. LinkedIn's algorithm improves its recommendations over time based on the jobs you save, apply to, and engage with. Review your alerts daily and apply to relevant positions within the first 24 to 48 hours, as LinkedIn data shows that candidates who apply within the first day are significantly more likely to get a response.\n"
"\n"
"Engage actively with content in your industry by commenting on posts, sharing articles, and publishing your own insights. This engagement increases your profile visibility in recruiter searches and positions you as a thought leader in your field. Many job opportunities come through connections formed through content engagement rather than direct job applications."
msgstr ""
"LinkedIn has evolved from a professional networking site into the most comprehensive job search platform available, combining job listings, recruiter access, company research, and professional networking in a single ecosystem. Optimizing your LinkedIn presence is no longer optional for job seekers; it is the foundation of a modern job search strategy.\n"
