#: src/data/wiki/categories/ats-optimization.ts
msgid "No, do not include a photo on your resume when applying through an ATS. Photos cannot be parsed by the system and may cause formatting issues. In many countries, including the United States, Canada, and the United Kingdom, photos on resumes are discouraged because they can introduce unconscious bias into the hiring process. Some ATS platforms may even flag resumes with photos as potentially problematic. If you want to share your professional image, keep it on your LinkedIn profile, which recruiters will typically review separately."
msgstr "No, do not include a photo on your resume when applying through an ATS. Photos cannot be parsed by the system and may cause formatting issues. In many countries, including the United States, Canada, and the United Kingdom, photos on resumes are discouraged because they can introduce unconscious bias into the hiring process. Some ATS platforms may even flag resumes with photos as potentially problematic. If you want to share your professional image, keep it on your LinkedIn profile, which recruiters will typically review separately."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-fundamentals.ts
msgid "No, lying on a resume is never acceptable and can have serious consequences. Fabricating degrees, inflating job titles, inventing certifications, or falsifying employment dates can result in immediate termination if discovered after hiring, and many companies conduct thorough background checks. Beyond the professional risk, dishonesty on a resume can damage your reputation permanently in your industry. Instead of lying, focus on presenting your genuine qualifications in the strongest possible light through strategic framing and quantified achievements."
msgstr "No, lying on a resume is never acceptable and can have serious consequences. Fabricating degrees, inflating job titles, inventing certifications, or falsifying employment dates can result in immediate termination if discovered after hiring, and many companies conduct thorough background checks. Beyond the professional risk, dishonesty on a resume can damage your reputation permanently in your industry. Instead of lying, focus on presenting your genuine qualifications in the strongest possible light through strategic framing and quantified achievements."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/interview-preparation.ts
msgid "No, memorizing answers word for word can make you sound robotic and leaves you vulnerable if the question is phrased differently than expected. Instead, memorize key bullet points and practice delivering them conversationally. Focus on the core message, key metrics, and the structure of your stories. Natural delivery is far more impressive than a rehearsed script."
msgstr "No, memorizing answers word for word can make you sound robotic and leaves you vulnerable if the question is phrased differently than expected. Instead, memorize key bullet points and practice delivering them conversationally. Focus on the core message, key metrics, and the structure of your stories. Natural delivery is far more impressive than a rehearsed script."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/cover-letters.ts
msgid "No, you should not mention salary expectations in your cover letter unless the job posting specifically asks you to include them. Bringing up compensation before you have established your value through the interview process puts you at a disadvantage in negotiations. If the application requires salary expectations, include them in a separate line after your closing rather than weaving them into the paragraph itself."
msgstr "No, you should not mention salary expectations in your cover letter unless the job posting specifically asks you to include them. Bringing up compensation before you have established your value through the interview process puts you at a disadvantage in negotiations. If the application requires salary expectations, include them in a separate line after your closing rather than weaving them into the paragraph itself."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-sections.ts
msgid "No. A generic summary significantly reduces your chances of passing ATS screening and capturing recruiter interest. Tailor your summary for each application by incorporating keywords from the job description and emphasizing the qualifications most relevant to that specific role. You can keep a master summary and adjust key phrases for each submission."
msgstr "No. A generic summary significantly reduces your chances of passing ATS screening and capturing recruiter interest. Tailor your summary for each application by incorporating keywords from the job description and emphasizing the qualifications most relevant to that specific role. You can keep a master summary and adjust key phrases for each submission."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/job-search-strategies.ts
msgid "No. Asking for a job during an informational interview violates the implicit agreement and damages trust. The informational interview should focus on learning and building a relationship. If you impress the person, they will naturally think of you when relevant opportunities arise or offer to make introductions. The indirect approach consistently produces better results than the direct ask."
msgstr "No. Asking for a job during an informational interview violates the implicit agreement and damages trust. The informational interview should focus on learning and building a relationship. If you impress the person, they will naturally think of you when relevant opportunities arise or offer to make introductions. The indirect approach consistently produces better results than the direct ask."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/career-transitions.ts
msgid "No. Select three to five of your most impressive or relevant clients and highlight those. Consolidate your freelance experience under a single professional heading with a date range, then feature key projects underneath. Listing every client creates clutter and dilutes the impact of your strongest work. Focus on quality and relevance to your target role."
msgstr "No. Select three to five of your most impressive or relevant clients and highlight those. Consolidate your freelance experience under a single professional heading with a date range, then feature key projects underneath. Listing every client creates clutter and dilutes the impact of your strongest work. Focus on quality and relevance to your target role."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-sections.ts
msgid "No. Using both is redundant and wastes space. Choose one format based on your situation. If you want elements of both, use a hybrid statement that opens with a professional overview and closes with a targeted career goal. This gives you the benefits of both formats in a single, concise paragraph."
msgstr "No. Using both is redundant and wastes space. Choose one format based on your situation. If you want elements of both, use a hybrid statement that opens with a professional overview and closes with a targeted career goal. This gives you the benefits of both formats in a single, concise paragraph."

