"\n"
"The work experience section is the heart of your chronological resume. List each position starting with your most recent role. For each entry, include your job title, the name of the company, the location of the company, and your dates of employment. Below these details, include four to six bullet points describing your responsibilities and achievements. Use strong action verbs to begin each bullet point, and quantify your accomplishments wherever possible. Instead of writing \"responsible for managing a team,\" write \"led a team of 12 engineers, delivering three major product releases on schedule and under budget.\"\n"
