msgid "The reverse chronological format remains the most popular and widely accepted resume format in 2026. It is preferred by the majority of recruiters and hiring managers and is optimized for applicant tracking systems. However, the combination format has been gaining popularity, particularly among career changers and professionals with diverse skill sets. The best format for you depends on your individual circumstances rather than general popularity trends."
