#: src/data/wiki/categories/ats-optimization.ts
msgid "There is no fixed number, but a well-optimized resume typically includes 25 to 40 relevant keywords that are naturally distributed across all sections. Focus on quality over quantity: include every keyword from the job description that genuinely matches your experience. Primary keywords that appear in the required qualifications should be mentioned two to three times across different sections. Less critical keywords can appear once. The key is natural integration. If your resume reads well to a human while containing relevant terms, you have the right balance."
msgstr "There is no fixed number, but a well-optimized resume typically includes 25 to 40 relevant keywords that are naturally distributed across all sections. Focus on quality over quantity: include every keyword from the job description that genuinely matches your experience. Primary keywords that appear in the required qualifications should be mentioned two to three times across different sections. Less critical keywords can appear once. The key is natural integration. If your resume reads well to a human while containing relevant terms, you have the right balance."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/career-transitions.ts
msgid "There is no fixed threshold that disqualifies a candidate. Gaps of two to five years are common and well understood by most employers. Even longer gaps can be overcome with the right approach: updated skills, relevant certifications, volunteer experience, and a strong narrative about your readiness to return. The key is demonstrating current relevance, not the length of the gap itself."
msgstr "There is no fixed threshold that disqualifies a candidate. Gaps of two to five years are common and well understood by most employers. Even longer gaps can be overcome with the right approach: updated skills, relevant certifications, volunteer experience, and a strong narrative about your readiness to return. The key is demonstrating current relevance, not the length of the gap itself."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/networking-linkedin.ts
msgid "There is no magic number. Research suggests that most professionals benefit from maintaining approximately 150 active relationships, but even a well-cultivated network of 30 to 50 genuine connections can be more valuable than thousands of superficial ones. Focus on building diverse connections across industries, seniority levels, and functions rather than accumulating a high connection count. A smaller network of people who know you well and would actively recommend you is far more powerful than a large network of acquaintances."
msgstr "There is no magic number. Research suggests that most professionals benefit from maintaining approximately 150 active relationships, but even a well-cultivated network of 30 to 50 genuine connections can be more valuable than thousands of superficial ones. Focus on building diverse connections across industries, seniority levels, and functions rather than accumulating a high connection count. A smaller network of people who know you well and would actively recommend you is far more powerful than a large network of acquaintances."

