#: src/data/wiki/categories/ats-optimization.ts
msgid "Two-column layouts are risky for ATS compatibility. Many ATS parsers read content in a single linear stream from top to bottom. A two-column layout can cause the parser to interleave or merge content from both columns, resulting in garbled output. While some modern ATS platforms handle multi-column layouts better than older ones, the safest approach is a single-column layout. If you want visual appeal, use a two-column layout for networking copies but maintain a single-column version for online applications."
msgstr "Two-column layouts are risky for ATS compatibility. Many ATS parsers read content in a single linear stream from top to bottom. A two-column layout can cause the parser to interleave or merge content from both columns, resulting in garbled output. While some modern ATS platforms handle multi-column layouts better than older ones, the safest approach is a single-column layout. If you want visual appeal, use a two-column layout for networking copies but maintain a single-column version for online applications."

