#: src/data/wiki/categories/ats-optimization.ts
msgid "Yes, absolutely. Many professional resume designers prioritize visual impact over ATS compatibility. Beautifully designed resumes with custom layouts, graphics, tables, and creative formatting often perform poorly in ATS systems. If your professionally designed resume uses multi-column layouts, text boxes, images, or non-standard section headings, it may fail to parse correctly. Ask your designer specifically about ATS compatibility, or maintain a separate ATS-optimized version of your resume for online applications. Use creative designs only for networking and in-person opportunities."
msgstr "Yes, absolutely. Many professional resume designers prioritize visual impact over ATS compatibility. Beautifully designed resumes with custom layouts, graphics, tables, and creative formatting often perform poorly in ATS systems. If your professionally designed resume uses multi-column layouts, text boxes, images, or non-standard section headings, it may fail to parse correctly. Ask your designer specifically about ATS compatibility, or maintain a separate ATS-optimized version of your resume for online applications. Use creative designs only for networking and in-person opportunities."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-formats.ts
msgid "Yes, and this approach is called a combination or hybrid resume. It is increasingly popular because it allows you to lead with a skills section that highlights your most relevant competencies while still including a chronological work history section that provides context and credibility. The combination format addresses the main weakness of the functional resume, which is the lack of context for your accomplishments, while still giving you the flexibility to emphasize your skills."
msgstr "Yes, and this approach is called a combination or hybrid resume. It is increasingly popular because it allows you to lead with a skills section that highlights your most relevant competencies while still including a chronological work history section that provides context and credibility. The combination format addresses the main weakness of the functional resume, which is the lack of context for your accomplishments, while still giving you the flexibility to emphasize your skills."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-formats.ts
msgid "Yes, combination resumes are generally ATS-compatible because they include the standard chronological work history section that ATS systems are designed to parse. The addition of a skills section at the top does not confuse most modern ATS software. To maximize compatibility, use standard section headings, avoid tables or complex formatting, and include relevant keywords from the job description throughout both the skills and experience sections."
msgstr "Yes, combination resumes are generally ATS-compatible because they include the standard chronological work history section that ATS systems are designed to parse. The addition of a skills section at the top does not confuse most modern ATS software. To maximize compatibility, use standard section headings, avoid tables or complex formatting, and include relevant keywords from the job description throughout both the skills and experience sections."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/industry-guides.ts
msgid "Yes, cover letters remain expected for most finance positions, particularly at banks, accounting firms, and corporate finance departments. A strong cover letter allows you to explain your specific interest in the firm and role, contextualize career transitions, and demonstrate written communication skills. Keep it concise, ideally three to four paragraphs, and tailor it to each application rather than using a generic template."
msgstr "Yes, cover letters remain expected for most finance positions, particularly at banks, accounting firms, and corporate finance departments. A strong cover letter allows you to explain your specific interest in the firm and role, contextualize career transitions, and demonstrate written communication skills. Keep it concise, ideally three to four paragraphs, and tailor it to each application rather than using a generic template."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/ats-optimization.ts
msgid "Yes, depending on how the employer has configured the system. Some ATS platforms allow employers to set minimum score thresholds or knockout questions that automatically disqualify candidates who do not meet basic requirements. However, many companies configure their ATS to rank rather than reject, meaning a recruiter can still access lower-scoring resumes if they choose to. The safest approach is to optimize your resume so it scores well regardless of the system's configuration."
msgstr "Yes, depending on how the employer has configured the system. Some ATS platforms allow employers to set minimum score thresholds or knockout questions that automatically disqualify candidates who do not meet basic requirements. However, many companies configure their ATS to rank rather than reject, meaning a recruiter can still access lower-scoring resumes if they choose to. The safest approach is to optimize your resume so it scores well regardless of the system's configuration."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/industry-guides.ts
msgid "Yes, especially if you are a new graduate or have fewer than two years of post-licensure experience. List each rotation with the facility name, unit type, hours completed, and key skills developed. As you gain more professional experience, clinical rotations can be condensed or moved to an education subsection."
msgstr "Yes, especially if you are a new graduate or have fewer than two years of post-licensure experience. List each rotation with the facility name, unit type, hours completed, and key skills developed. As you gain more professional experience, clinical rotations can be condensed or moved to an education subsection."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-sections.ts
msgid "Yes, especially if you are a recent graduate or early in your career. Professors who supervised your research, capstone projects, or internships can provide credible references about your work ethic, analytical skills, and potential. As your career progresses, aim to replace academic references with professional ones from supervisors and colleagues."
msgstr "Yes, especially if you are a recent graduate or early in your career. Professors who supervised your research, capstone projects, or internships can provide credible references about your work ethic, analytical skills, and potential. As your career progresses, aim to replace academic references with professional ones from supervisors and colleagues."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/salary-negotiation.ts
msgid "Yes, even companies with standardized benefits often have flexibility, especially for senior hires. While health insurance plans and retirement matching may be truly fixed, signing bonuses, equity grants, PTO above the standard allotment, and professional development budgets are frequently negotiable. The key is asking, because many candidates assume everything is fixed when it is not."
msgstr "Yes, even companies with standardized benefits often have flexibility, especially for senior hires. While health insurance plans and retirement matching may be truly fixed, signing bonuses, equity grants, PTO above the standard allotment, and professional development budgets are frequently negotiable. The key is asking, because many candidates assume everything is fixed when it is not."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/ats-optimization.ts
msgid "Yes, for maximum ATS compatibility, use the exact terminology from the job description wherever possible. If the posting says \"project management,\" use \"project management\" rather than \"managing projects.\" If it mentions a specific tool like \"Salesforce CRM,\" use that exact phrase. However, also include common variations and abbreviations, such as writing out \"Search Engine Optimization (SEO)\" on first use. This covers both exact-match and semantic-match algorithms. Always ensure that any keyword you include truthfully represents your skills and experience."
msgstr "Yes, for maximum ATS compatibility, use the exact terminology from the job description wherever possible. If the posting says \"project management,\" use \"project management\" rather than \"managing projects.\" If it mentions a specific tool like \"Salesforce CRM,\" use that exact phrase. However, also include common variations and abbreviations, such as writing out \"Search Engine Optimization (SEO)\" on first use. This covers both exact-match and semantic-match algorithms. Always ensure that any keyword you include truthfully represents your skills and experience."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/remote-work.ts
msgid "Yes, having notes nearby is one advantage of virtual interviews. Place key talking points, company research, and questions on a small note next to your camera so you can reference them without obviously looking away. Avoid reading directly from notes, as this is noticeable on camera. Use them as memory prompts for prepared stories and data points, not as a script to read verbatim."
msgstr "Yes, having notes nearby is one advantage of virtual interviews. Place key talking points, company research, and questions on a small note next to your camera so you can reference them without obviously looking away. Avoid reading directly from notes, as this is noticeable on camera. Use them as memory prompts for prepared stories and data points, not as a script to read verbatim."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-sections.ts
msgid "Yes, if the certification is relevant to the target role and you are actively working toward it. List it with \"In Progress\" or \"Expected [Month Year]\" to set clear expectations. This shows initiative and signals that you will soon hold the credential. However, do not list certifications you have only vaguely planned to pursue someday."
msgstr "Yes, if the certification is relevant to the target role and you are actively working toward it. List it with \"In Progress\" or \"Expected [Month Year]\" to set clear expectations. This shows initiative and signals that you will soon hold the credential. However, do not list certifications you have only vaguely planned to pursue someday."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/networking-linkedin.ts
msgid "Yes, if you meet approximately 60 to 70 percent of the listed requirements. Job descriptions often represent an ideal candidate rather than a minimum requirement. Skills can be learned, and transferable experience from different industries or roles can be equally valuable. Focus your application on the requirements you do meet, explain how your transferable skills compensate for any gaps, and express enthusiasm for growing in the areas where you have less experience."
msgstr "Yes, if you meet approximately 60 to 70 percent of the listed requirements. Job descriptions often represent an ideal candidate rather than a minimum requirement. Skills can be learned, and transferable experience from different industries or roles can be equally valuable. Focus your application on the requirements you do meet, explain how your transferable skills compensate for any gaps, and express enthusiasm for growing in the areas where you have less experience."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/industry-guides.ts
msgid "Yes, if your GitHub profile contains relevant, well-maintained repositories that demonstrate your coding ability. Ensure your pinned repositories are current, well-documented, and representative of the work you want to be known for. If your GitHub is sparse or contains only forked repositories with no contributions, it may be better to omit it or create a few meaningful projects before including it."
msgstr "Yes, if your GitHub profile contains relevant, well-maintained repositories that demonstrate your coding ability. Ensure your pinned repositories are current, well-documented, and representative of the work you want to be known for. If your GitHub is sparse or contains only forked repositories with no contributions, it may be better to omit it or create a few meaningful projects before including it."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/salary-negotiation.ts
msgid "Yes, in most cases. Even a fair offer typically has some negotiation room built in, and a polite, well-researched counter demonstrates professionalism. You can acknowledge the offer is competitive while asking if there is flexibility on specific components. Even small gains in base salary compound significantly over your career."
msgstr "Yes, in most cases. Even a fair offer typically has some negotiation room built in, and a polite, well-researched counter demonstrates professionalism. You can acknowledge the offer is competitive while asking if there is flexibility on specific components. Even small gains in base salary compound significantly over your career."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/industry-guides.ts
msgid "Yes, include your union affiliation, local number, and membership status, especially when applying to union shops or projects with prevailing wage requirements. Union membership signals formal training, adherence to industry standards, and access to a verified dispatch system. For non-union applications, you may still include it as it demonstrates professional commitment, though it is not required."
msgstr "Yes, include your union affiliation, local number, and membership status, especially when applying to union shops or projects with prevailing wage requirements. Union membership signals formal training, adherence to industry standards, and access to a verified dispatch system. For non-union applications, you may still include it as it demonstrates professional commitment, though it is not required."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-sections.ts
msgid "Yes, particularly if the courses are from recognized institutions or platforms and are directly relevant to the position. For one or two courses, the education section works fine. If you have many, consider a separate \"Professional Development\" or \"Certifications\" section to keep the education section focused on formal degrees."
msgstr "Yes, particularly if the courses are from recognized institutions or platforms and are directly relevant to the position. For one or two courses, the education section works fine. If you have many, consider a separate \"Professional Development\" or \"Certifications\" section to keep the education section focused on formal degrees."

