#: src/data/wiki/categories/cover-letters.ts
msgid ""
"Your closing paragraph is your final opportunity to leave a strong impression, and many candidates underestimate its importance. A weak closing -- such as simply thanking the reader -- fails to capitalize on the momentum you have built throughout the letter. Instead, your conclusion should accomplish three things: reiterate your value proposition, express genuine enthusiasm for the opportunity, and include a clear call to action.\n"
"\n"
"Start by briefly summarizing why you are an excellent fit for the role. This does not mean repeating everything you have already said, but rather distilling your key message into one or two punchy sentences. For example: \"With a decade of experience driving product innovation at scale and a deep passion for user-centered design, I am confident I can help [Company Name] achieve its goal of becoming the market leader in accessible technology.\"\n"
"\n"
"Next, convey your excitement about the opportunity in a way that feels authentic. Avoid generic phrases like \"I would be thrilled to work for your company.\" Instead, reference something specific you learned during your research: \"The opportunity to contribute to your expansion into the European market is particularly exciting to me, given my experience launching products in three European countries.\"\n"
"\n"
"Finally, include a proactive call to action. Rather than passively waiting, signal your intent to follow up: \"I would welcome the opportunity to discuss how my experience aligns with your team's goals. I will follow up next week, but please do not hesitate to reach out at your convenience.\" This demonstrates initiative without being pushy.\n"
"\n"
"Close with a professional sign-off such as \"Sincerely,\" \"Best regards,\" or \"Respectfully,\" followed by your full name. If submitting a physical letter or a PDF, include a handwritten or digital signature for a polished touch."
msgstr ""
